cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use ctl-python in academic work, please cite it via the metadata below.
type: software
title: ctl-python
abstract: >-
  Native Python bindings for the CTL (Color Transformation Language)
  interpreter. Provides a pybind11 extension that calls libIlmCtl
  in-process, so applying CTL transforms to NumPy arrays no longer
  requires shelling out to a subprocess or moving data through
  intermediate EXR files. Caches loaded interpreters across calls and
  invalidates on .ctl mtime change (including transitively imported
  modules) so iterative CTL development in Python does not pay
  repeated module-parse overhead.
authors:
  - family-names: Forsythe
    given-names: Alex
repository-code: https://github.com/aforsythe/ctl-python
keywords:
  - color science
  - CTL
  - Color Transformation Language
  - ACES
  - Python
  - pybind11
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-04-27
